description:
GROUNDBREAKING COMICS WRITER GARTH ENNIS BRINGS CLASSIC DAN DARE BACK TO LIFE IN A BOLD NEW SERIES! Virgin Comics is compiling the first three issues of the landmark Dan Dare, written by Garth Ennis, into a Special Hardcover Edition. Whether you're joining the adventure for the first time, or a collector, this volume containing Dan Dare #1, #2 and #3 is the perfect addition to your comics Library. The 80-page hardcover book contains the first three issues with interior artwork by Gary Erskine, and the four covers from Bryan Talbot, Greg Horn, Jonathan Higgins, Brendan McCarthy and Garry Leach. Dan Dare was once a hero. He brokered peace with alien races, pushed the frontiers of space, and saved the planet from total annihilation... repeatedly. But now, his Space Fleet has disbanded, the United Nations has crumbled, his friends scattered to the solar winds. Britain is once again the world power, but Dare, disillusioned and disappointed in his once-precious home country, has quietly retired. But there's trouble mustering in Deep Space. The H.M.S. Achilles is picking up strange signals when, suddenly, an enormous fleet of hostile ships ambushes the destroyer. As the crew struggles to stay alive, they realize with horror that the hostiles have brought a weapon of unimaginable power. Dan Dare, pilot of the future, has been called out of retirement.

Dan Dare hardcover reprint collection of the first three issues of the Virgin Comics series.
name: Dan Dare Collectors Edition

description: The searing final arc starts here in "Trail's End" part one. Beginning months after last issue's shocking finale, we pick up with the citizens of the Prairie Rose Rez, some of whom have found a peace they never could have imagined, while others are in more trouble than ever – with at least one person plotting his next move from behind bars.
name: Trail's End, Part One

description: The vampires are among us, but it’s not always a question of supernatural creatures. Sometimes they’re just slightly eccentric young guys with a taste for gothic parties. Unluckily for them, however, in New England there exists a brotherhood of vampire exterminators who are none too gentle in their approach: as the exterminators see it, anyone they regard as “different” deserves to be eliminated. So that’s how it comes about that it falls to Harlan, this time, to get revenge for the self-styled blood-suckers, but he’s not all alone in his struggle, because out there in the old Druro lighthouse, where the coast of Cape Cod is at its most rugged, a thousand-year-old Entity will do its best to make the ruthless Vampire Slayers feel the chills of genuine Evil tingling down their spines…
name: Gli Ammazzavampiri

description: On the battlefields of the First World War, old myths die and new ones are born: The Crucified Soldier. The Comrade in White. The Corpse Factory. The Poison Rain. As the balance between reality and fiction tilts crazily in the crucible of war, a young Wilson Taylor has an experience that will change his life forever.
name: The Whisper Line

description: Along the course of the Armanack, towards Witch’s Gorge and Desolate Valley, the one-time dwelling place of the witch Asenath Prynn. This, indeed, is the risky itinerary followed by Harlan in his endeavor to get to the heart of the mystery about the curse those lands are under, where the descendants of ancient witch hunters live in the wilds in abject wretchedness. For amid the deep forests, nothing is as it should be: neither the trees, nor the animals, nor the members of the monstrous Pickering family…
name: Il fiume dell'orrore

description: In her holiday home, in the forest of Finnish Karelia, little Adina is obsessed by the personality of her beautiful aunt Ajna, who was killed in the Second World War. She talks to her, dreams she is actually her aunt, and is absolutely determined to find her a partner. Harlan Draka is also a guest of Villa Valkea, but who is this Aunt Ajna, really? A romantic legend, an unhappy ghost or a voracious vampire?
name: La signora della villa bianca

description: In romantic Istanbul, Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak are on the tracks of a self-styled vampire and find themselves bang in the middle of a mafia-type war. One of the killers is Yacek, an old acquaintance of Kurjak’s, a one-time sniper who’s now turned into a hired killer in the pay of the Turkish mafia. He’s a restless loner carrying a burden of grief in his heart, tormented by an immortal lover that feeds on the pain of her victims: tragic and mysterious Adara…
name: L'ultima notte

description: In the lands that lie “at the edge of the world”, as the most remote provinces of Angola are called, there is a sinister rumor afoot: the “Doctor”, the head of the anti-government guerillas who died on the battlefield, is back at the head of his men. And behind the formation that has hoisted high the ensign of the “Galo Negro” a dreaded figure looms up, hideously - the shadow of Jan Vathek! Harlan, Tesla and Kurjak, who have followed the tracks of their enemy all the way to Angola, once more join up with the plucky volunteers of the Medical Team in the desperate attempt to stop the war from gaining the upper hand again…
name: Vathek!

description: True Love soars once again, as Machi emerges from her rite of passage. And the return of every body's favorite badass Cyborg... Batan.
name: Wings Of The Righteous

description:
LANDMARK ANNIVERSARY ISSUE!

Just in time for the release of THE DARKNESS II video game from 2K Games and Digital Extremes, Top Cow proudly releases the over-sized 100th issue of one of their flagship characters. Long time writer PHIL HESTER (Wonder Woman, Green Hornet) concludes his epic run on the series with artist ROMANO MOLENAAR (THE DARKNESS II : CONFESSION) as Darkness bearer, Jackie Estacado comes face-to-face with the source of his power and misery - the Darkness itself! And only one of them will walk away...
name: Total Darkness, Part Five: The Darkness

description: Reprints political cartoons, Joe Bob Briggs and Ian Shoales columns, and comic strips: Calvin & Hobbes, The Far Side, Outland, Doonesbury, and Life In Hell (Matt Groening)

Ellis describes the creation of Simon Spector as a cross between Doc Savage, The Shadow, and The Spider. "These were the guys who didn't screw around. And did they turn the bad guys over to the cops? Did they hell. They shredded the bad guys with hails of bullets, often from machine pistols they designed themselves to kill the bad guys more quickly and more messily. At best they abducted the bad guys and performed back room brain surgery on them to make them better citizens. And then they'd go home to play the violin badly, shag their secret mistresses and, in Doc Savage's case, play with a little box of vials that even as a kid I was convinced contained drugs of some kind. For those of us who loved the pulp heroes, but thought that back then things were a little too coy and way too white, I give you Simon Spector: superhuman detective adventurer who is also, frankly, here to take drugs and kill people."

name: Kalle och vinden från Södern
Kalle Kalle Anka

description: It's the stunning conclusion of OPERATION: ANNIHILATE! The events of the new timeline unfold in shocking ways as Kirk reunites with his estranged brother to save a colony from extinction. STAR TREK writer/producer Roberto Orci oversees this story that continues the lead-up to the much-anticipated film sequel!
name: Operation: Annihilate! Part 2

description:
Tamsin & Kitsune's use of the Skeleton Key gets them further into trouble when a giant cat relocates to their suburban home. this triggers a series of events that lead to lost friendships. revealed secrets and the production of counterfeit money.

Collects Skeleton Key #25-30.
name: Cats & Dogs

description: The Subterraneans have been fighting among themselves for decades, but now they've been united by a dangerous leader. The T.H.U.N.D.E.R. Agents are humanity's best hope at stopping this looming threat, but how can they when the team is falling apart at the seams? Featuring a sequence by guest artist Sam Kieth!
name: The Long Con

description:
The stirring prequel to the award-winning, bestselling BONE series!

When a terrifying dragon attacks the small towns of the Northern Valley, a young Princess Rose (known later as Gran'ma Ben) must defeat it. The beast is actually the ancient evil, the Lord of the Locusts, and while Rose faces danger with honor, her elder sister, Princess Briar, follows a more sinister path.

An unforgettable story with beautiful, sweeping artwork, this prequel explores the fateful beginnings of the epic BONE saga.

Back Blurb

A terrifying dragon lays siege to the small towns of the Northern Valley. Unknown to Princess Rose, who must defeat the gigantic beast, the dragon is actually the ancient evil Lord of the Locusts. Unable to defeat the monster, Rose seeks the advice of her advisors, who tells the princess how to destroy the dragon --- but at a terrible cost...
name: Rose

description: This is the ultimate handbook for every BONE fan! Includes character profiles, a timeline of events, interviews with creator Jeff Smith and colorist Steve Hamaker, a showcase of cover art from the original BONE editions, a behind-the-scenes look at how the Scholastic editions were colorized, and other fun stuff!
name: Handbook

description: Continuing the series based on the best-selling PS3 game! With the real enemy revealed, Drake and Chloe are on the run in the center of the earth and on their way to the lost city of Agartha! But deep in the darkness…something is watching them.

What pushes someone to hurt the people they love? Eric has shown us that his capacity for evil is limitless, but is something else to blame? Find out as Eric confronts Nicky in the final chapter of the critically acclaimed miniseries, The Cape, by the Eisner-nominated creative team of Jason Ciaramella, Joe Hill, Zach Howard, and Nelson Daniel. Explore your dark side.

In this special 40-page story, G.I. Joe is on the trail of a rogue unit of Crimson Guardsmen. But the Joes aren’t the only ones hunting down the renegade threat: Zartan and his Dreadnoks have been sent by COBRA to handle the situation. This could get ugly for the Joes! Written by Larry Hama, drawn by three classic artists, and inked by the legendary Sal Buscema, this is a G.I. Joe story you can’t miss!
name: Annual 2012

has_staff_review.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero Annual #1

volume.name: G.I. Joe: A Real American Hero Annual

description: Who kidnapped the Professor? Did a UFO land in New York City? Who is telling the truth about being abducted and who is lying? The answers to all those questions and more are in this issue as the Xenoholics are once again taken by aliens. But are the aliens friends... or Foes?
name: The Truth Is Here!

description: The tragic finale of Lost Children culminates with final retribution against one of Green Wake's occupants. Morley unlocks an integral clue to his first steps in uncovering Green Wake's earliest secrets.
name: Lost Children, Part 5

description: New York City is down but not out - the zombie apocalypse has destroyed much of the city, but hard-boiled humanity hangs on. But with the survivors divided into warring factions, and the undead hiding behind every corner, only one man can walk the streets alone: Nick Ewing. His murdered wife and child, from the grave, give him the strength to continue his vendetta against the king of Yankee Stadium. The complete collected hit series from Coheed and Cambria frontman Claudio Sanchez, Chondra Echert, hot new talent Aaron Kuder, and cover artist Nathan Fox.
name: TPB

description: Various tales of horror in 3-D
name: House of Terror

description: The “brains” of the Turtles steps out on his own in this unique tale! Intrigued by a cutting-edge science fair, Donatello goes incognito in public to get his fill of the latest tech. Little does he know that the fair is hosted by none other than Baxter Stockman—and he's holding a competition to see who can create the best gizmo to find the Turtles first! It's up to Don to out-geek the geeks, all while keeping his cover! Don't miss this awesome, fun-filled adventure!
name: Donatello
